summary: 10+ years in IT and then 10+ years in quality management... So far and at the same time so close. Both of them demand from you to collect information and analyze, change processes and train people, be logical and patient. When you write program you organize code, when you write instruction you organize text. When you write program you need to understand work flow and you can not change quality management system without understanding what and why you want to do. When you write program you should keep in mind that it cannot work itself without operators, when you try to do something in the best way you also need to include common people in your "great" ideas. So that is my work - to change quality through changing code of life...
